Full Stack Principal Software Engineer - Middle Office Technology

Experienced full stack developer to work within agile software development practice delivering financial software globally. In this role, you will be not only be designing and coding, but mentoring other developers to help build a world class software engineering capability within the Middle Office Technology Group.

Job responsibilities and opportunities:

Drive the design and implementation of scalable, high performing and robust applications.

Proactively manage changes in project scope, identify potential issues, and devise contingency plans.

Improve our software delivery capabilities via automation and repeatability

Provide technical mentorship and guidance to more junior engineers including code reviews and diving in to coding assignments when necessary as well as defining and implementing best in class standards.

Help the tech management team shape best practices for developing, sharing and continuously improving our software platform.

Identifying issues to teams that they might overlook, such as scalability, performance, or security.

Coordinate with internal and external technology teams as needed for end to end service delivery.

Consult and collaborate with internal business partners to construct and execute on our service delivery strategy and ensure compliance with the firm's delivery and regulatory standards.

Active participation in open source community with contributions to one or more projects, with code available for inspection.

Expertise in test driven and behavior driven development

At least 3 years of experience with agile software development methodologies, tools and processes.

Knowledge of orchestration of microservices in an elastic container-based cloud environment

Experience in the financial services sector a plus.

Requirements:

Bachelor's degree in computer science engineering or a related discipline or equivalent work experience required

10-12 years of experience in software engineering required in any modern software development platform including Java, C# or Python. Ruby on Rails preferred but not required.

Technical Skills:

Our current stack includes Ruby, Rails, Active Record, RSpec, Cucumber and Docker. We use both Postgres and Oracle as our RDBMS and IBM WMQ and Rabbit MQ for messaging. For the UI were using AngularJS, React and Bootstrap CSS and our tool stack includes GIT, Jenkins, TeamCity, JIRA and Confluence.

