TECHNOLOGY SERVICES GROUP (TSG) is the central infrastructure services group with a proven track record of innovating to help BNY Mellon and its customers have most reliable, nimble and cost-effective solutions in the financial services market place. BNY Mellon App Engine technology is leading edge with industry first PasS/IaaS fully integrated solution, combined with enterprise standards for developers.

TSG is building next generation scalable, efficient data center as a service using the latest innovation infrastructure. Building on top of the cloud deployments in BNY Mellon, we are aggressively automating and bridging the green field cloud with the existing virtual computing environments.

The employee will be participating in full stack development for IDIP (the Configuration Management DB for the organization). The software is widely used throughout the organization, providing a catalog of both the IT assets as well as the organization's Application portfolio. Two technology stacks are currently maintained in parallel with the ultimate goal being the Java/Angular based product replacing the older Coldfusion based offering. Instantiation of new features will need to be performed in both environments.

Job Responsibilities:

Development of web pages in both Coldfusion and Java/Angular based systems.

Development of Oracle database objects tables/views/stored procedures/etc.

Requirements gathering with clients to define interfaces providing new sources of data.

Development of proactive safety checks to detect outages in both the core system as well as interfaces.

Provide technical backing to operations staff to ensure proper functionality as well as meeting of SLAs in the case of outages.

